---
import BaseLayout from "@/layouts/BaseLayout.astro";

const updated = "October 26, 2025"; // keep this current
---

<BaseLayout
    title="Terms of Service — AHS Ratings"
    description="The terms that govern your use of AHS Ratings."
>
    <section class="container py-10">
        <h1
            class="mb-2 text-3xl font-bold"
            style="font-family: var(--font-display)"
        >
            Terms of Service
        </h1>
        <p class="text-muted">Last updated: {updated}</p>

        <div class="mt-8 space-y-8">
            <section class="space-y-3">
                <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold">Acceptance of terms</h2>
                <p class="text-muted">
                    By accessing or using AHS Ratings (the “Service”), you agree
                    to these Terms of Service and our
                    <a href="/privacy" class="underline text-text"
                        >Privacy Policy</a
                    >. If you do not agree, do not use the Service.
                </p>
            </section>

            <section class="space-y-3">
                <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold">Eligibility & accounts</h2>
                <ul class="list-disc space-y-2 pl-6 text-muted">
                    <li>
                        You must be at least 13 years old (or the minimum age in
                        your country) to use the Service.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        You’re responsible for your account and keeping your
                        credentials secure.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        You must provide accurate information and promptly
                        update it (e.g., verified email, username).
                    </li>
                </ul>
            </section>

            <section class="space-y-3">
                <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold">Usernames & profiles</h2>
                <p class="text-muted">
                    Usernames must be unique, at least 5 characters, and use
                    letters, numbers, or underscores. We may reclaim or remove
                    usernames that impersonate others, violate rights, or break
                    these Terms.
                </p>
            </section>

            <section class="space-y-3">
                <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold">Your content</h2>
                <p class="text-muted">
                    “Content” includes ratings, usernames, profile photos, and
                    any text you submit. You retain rights to your Content. By
                    submitting Content, you grant us a worldwide, non-exclusive,
                    royalty-free license to host, store, reproduce, display, and
                    distribute that Content for operating and improving the
                    Service (e.g., rendering your chart, calculating community
                    averages, and showing feeds).
                </p>
                <p class="text-muted">
                    You’re responsible for your Content and must have the
                    necessary rights to submit it. Do not post illegal,
                    infringing, or harmful material, or anything that violates
                    others’ rights or the law.
                </p>
            </section>

            <section class="space-y-3">
                <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold">Public display</h2>
                <p class="text-muted">
                    Your username and ratings may be visible to others on the
                    site (e.g., on your profile or in “Latest Ratings” and
                    “Stats”). Your email is not publicly displayed.
                </p>
            </section>

            <section class="space-y-3">
                <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold">Acceptable use</h2>
                <ul class="list-disc space-y-2 pl-6 text-muted">
                    <li>
                        No scraping, rate-limiting abuse, or attempting to
                        bypass security or RLS rules.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        No uploading malware, exploits, or attempting
                        unauthorized access.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        No harassment, hate speech, or content inciting
                        violence.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        No impersonation or misrepresentation of your identity
                        or affiliation.
                    </li>
                    <li>Respect intellectual property and privacy rights.</li>
                </ul>
            </section>

            <section class="space-y-3">
                <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold">Third-party services</h2>
                <p class="text-muted">
                    The Service integrates third-party services like Supabase
                    (auth, database, storage/CDN) and Netlify (hosting). OAuth
                    providers (e.g., Google) are optional for sign-in. Your use
                    of those services may be subject to their terms and privacy
                    policies.
                </p>
            </section>

            <section class="space-y-3">
                <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold">Termination</h2>
                <p class="text-muted">
                    You may stop using the Service at any time. We may suspend
                    or terminate access if you violate these Terms or if we
                    believe your use poses risk to the Service or others. Upon
                    termination, some provisions survive (e.g., disclaimers,
                    limitations of liability, and governing law).
                </p>
            </section>

            <section class="space-y-3">
                <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold">Disclaimers</h2>
                <p class="text-muted">
                    The Service is provided “as is” and “as available”. We
                    disclaim all warranties, express or implied, including
                    merchantability, fitness for a particular purpose, and
                    non-infringement. We do not warrant that the Service will be
                    uninterrupted, secure, or error-free.
                </p>
            </section>

            <section class="space-y-3">
                <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold">Limitation of liability</h2>
                <p class="text-muted">
                    To the maximum extent permitted by law, AHS Ratings and its
                    operators will not be liable for any indirect, incidental,
                    special, consequential, or punitive damages, or any lost
                    profits, revenues, data, or goodwill arising from or related
                    to your use of the Service.
                </p>
            </section>

            <section class="space-y-3">
                <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold">Governing law</h2>
                <p class="text-muted">
                    These Terms are governed by the laws of the jurisdiction
                    specified by the site operator. If you’re a consumer,
                    mandatory consumer protection rules of your country may also
                    apply. Venue and forum selection will follow applicable law.
                    (Replace this section with your specific jurisdiction if
                    needed.)
                </p>
            </section>

            <section class="space-y-3">
                <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold">Changes to these Terms</h2>
                <p class="text-muted">
                    We may update these Terms as we evolve the Service. We’ll
                    update the “Last updated” date and, when appropriate,
                    provide additional notice. By continuing to use the Service
                    after changes take effect, you accept the updated Terms.
                </p>
            </section>

            <section class="space-y-3">
                <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold">Contact</h2>
                <p class="text-muted">
                    Questions? Email <a
                        class="underline text-text"
                        href="mailto:support@ahsratings.example"
                        >support@ahsratings.example</a
                    >.
                </p>
            </section>
        </div>
    </section>
</BaseLayout>
